(1) The jurisdiction of a small claims court shall be limited to a small claim. [subsection (1) substituted by section 3 of Act 15 of 2025 ]
The jurisdiction of a small claims court shall be limited to a small claim. [subsection (1) substituted by section 3 of Act 15 of 2025 ]
(2) Despite the generality of subsection (1) , a small claims court shall have jurisdiction over a small claim arising from the following causes of action: (a) proceedings for the delivery of movable or immovable property whose value does not exceed the prescribed sum; (b) proceedings for debts that are due and payable; (c) proceedings for rentals that are due and payable in respect of premises; (d) proceedings for possession against the occupier of premises where the rent of occupation per month does not exceed the prescribed sum; (e) proceedings relating to, or arising out of a cheque or an acknowledgment of debt signed by a debtor; (f) proceedings of claims arising out of the Money Lender’s Act which does not exceed the prescribed sum; and [Cap. 398 ] (g) proceedings relating to prescribed liquidated employment claims whose value does not exceed the sum that the Chief Justice may, by statutory instrument, prescribe. [subsection (2) substituted by section 3 of Act 15 of 2025 ]
