(1) A commissioner shall hold office for a term of five years and may be re-appointed for a further and final term of five years.
A commissioner shall hold office for a term of five years and may be re-appointed for a further and final term of five years.
(2) The office of a commissioner becomes vacant if the commissioner— (a) dies; (b) resigns, by giving one month notice, in writing, to the Commission; (c) is legally disqualified from performing the functions of a commissioner; (d) is convicted of an offence under this Act or any other written law and sentenced to imprisonment for a term exceeding six months without the option of a fine; (e) is adjudged bankrupt; (f) is removed from office by the Commission on grounds of miscounduct or breach of trust; or (g) engages in active politics.
