(1) A person who is before a small claims court shall not— (a) threaten, intimidate or insult the small claims court while sitting in that capacity; (b) intentionally interrupt the proceedings of the small claims court or behave in a disorderly manner before the small claims court; (c) deliberately omit to deliver up a document or thing in accordance with an order of the small claims court; (d) refuse to answer a question asked by the small claims court; (e) while proceedings are in progress in the small claims court, make use of any speech or writing misrepresenting any proceedings of the small claims court in a way as to prejudice the commissioner in favour of, or against, any party to those proceedings; or (f) wilfully disobey or fail to comply with any lawful order of the small claims court.
